HEADWORD: misgiving
<hw>mis*giv"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Evil premonition; doubt;
distrust; a feeling of apprehension; -- used commonly in the
plural.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Suspicious and <xex>misgivings</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
